'''Amine Ferid Gouiri''' ({{langx|ar|أمين فريد قويري}}; born 16 February 2000) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] or [[left winger]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/amine-gouiri/454747/|title=A. Gouiri|website=Soccerway|access-date=19 November 2017}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Lyon===
A player of [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] starting in 2013, Gouiri signed his first professional contract with the club on 3 July 2017 for three years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.olweb.fr/fr/article/academie-comme-amine-gouiri-maxence-caqueret-signe-un-contrat-stagiaire-de-3-ans-31400.html|title=Académie : Comme Amine Gouiri, Maxence Caqueret signe un contrat stagiaire de 3 ans - OLWeb.fr|website=olweb.fr}}</ref>

An internationally renowned prospect, Gouiri made the bench for Lyon in a [[Ligue 1]] match against [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]] on 10 September 2016 at the age of 16, and debuted for the [[Olympique Lyonnais Reserves and Academy|Lyon B]] team at the age of 17.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fr.vavel.com/football/lyon/811374-qui-es-tu-amine-gouiri.html|title=Qui es-tu, Amine Gouiri ?|last=Vavel|date=27 July 2017|access-date=20 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201035701/https://fr.vavel.com/football/lyon/811374-qui-es-tu-amine-gouiri.html|archive-date=1 December 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his first team debut on 19 November 2017 in a 0–0 home draw against [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]] in [[Ligue 1]]. He entered the field after 73 minutes replacing [[Tanguy Ndombele]].<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/11/19/france/ligue-1/olympique-lyonnais/montpellier-herault-sport-club/2465031/|title=Lyon vs. Montpellier - 19 November 2017|website=Soccerway|access-date=19 November 2017}}</ref>

===Nice===
On 1 July 2020, Gouiri joined fellow [[Ligue 1]] side [[OGC Nice|Nice]] on a four-year contract for a fee of €7 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-amine-gouiri-ol-a-nice-officiel/1148785|title=Transferts : Amine Gouiri (OL) à Nice (officiel)|publisher=[[L'Équipe]]|date=2 July 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-sg/news/gouiri-has-shown-maturity-at-ogc-nice-hassane-kamara/pqd1x3561u031czsakz3ptl5s|title=Wonderkid Gouiri has shown maturity at OGC Nice - Hassane Kamara|website=Goal.com|date=22 August 2020}}</ref> On 23 August 2020, he scored two goals in his first competitive match for Nice, in a 2–1 league home win over newly promoted [[RC Lens|Lens]], becoming the club's youngest player in the last 70 years to have scored at least twice in his club debut in the French top flight.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-sg/news/gouiri-shatters-70-year-old-nice-record-with-brace-against/ktq91x73sxkl1lv3f5puvnu39|title=Gouiri shatters 70-year-old Nice record with brace against Lens|website=Goal.com|date=24 August 2020}}</ref> On 29 October 2020, he scored the only goal in a 1–0 win over [[Hapoel Be'er Sheva F.C.|Hapoel Be'er Sheva]] in the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2029745--nice-vs-h-beer-sheva/ |title=Nice 1–0 H. Beer-Sheva |website=UEFA |date=29 October 2020 }}</ref>

=== Rennes ===
On 1 September 2022, Gouiri joined [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] on a five-year contract until 30 June 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-09-01 |title=Amine Gouiri est Rouge et Noir ! |url=https://www.staderennais.com/amine-gouiri-est-rouge-et-noir |access-date=2022-09-04 |website=STADE RENNAIS F.C. |language=fr}}</ref>

=== Marseille ===
On 31 January 2025, Gouiri signed for [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] for a reported transfer fee of €22 million, bonuses included.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mercato : l'attaquant de Rennes Amine Gouiri officiellement à Marseille |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Mercato-l-attaquant-de-rennes-amine-gouiri-officiellement-a-marseille/1536740 |access-date=2025-01-31 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> On 27 April, Gouiri scored a hat trick, including an overhead kick, as Marseille beat [[Stade Brestois 29|Stade Brest]] 4-1 to reclaim second place in the league.<ref>{{cite news | url = https://sports.yahoo.com/article/gouiri-hat-trick-guides-marseille-213905729.html | title = Gouiri hat-trick guides Marseille back to second in Ligue 1 | date = 27 April 2025 }}</ref> He finished his first season with the club with 10 goals in 14 appearances.

==International career==
Gouiri was born in France and is of Algerian descent, and holds dual-citizenship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.2022mag.com/lyon-amine-gouiri-a-tout-dun-futur-grand/|title=Lyon: Amine Gouiri a tout d'un futur grand|date=27 May 2017}}</ref> He was a youth international for France, Gouiri was the top scorer at the [[2017 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]], scoring 7 goals and was the top scorer in the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/news/0252-0cda45d5436a-f0e234f4a228-1000--gouiri-takes-u17-euro-top-scorers-prize/|title=Under-17|date=19 May 2017|website=UEFA}}</ref> After his success in the tournament, Gouiri garnered the attention of various European clubs and was rated one of the best young talents in the world by ''[[The Guardian]]''.<ref>{{cite web|date=4 October 2017|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2017/oct/04/next-generation-2017-60-of-the-best-young-talents-in-world-football|title=Next Generation 2017: 60 of the best young talents in world football|work=The Guardian}}</ref>

Gouri also represented France at the [[2017 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] in [[India]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.20minutes.fr/sport/football/2148167-20171011-lyon-comment-attaquant-phare-mondial-u17-amine-gouiri-rappelle-karim-benzema-ol|title=Lyon: Comment l'attaquant phare du Mondial U17 Amine Gouiri "rappelle Karim Benzema" à l'OL|website=20minutes.fr|date=11 October 2017 }}</ref> scoring a brace in his debut in the tournament against the [[New Caledonia national under-17 football team|New Caledonia U17s]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u17worldcup/matches/round=275931/match=300394731/match-report.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171010233925/http://www.fifa.com/u17worldcup/matches/round=275931/match=300394731/match-report.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=October 10, 2017|title=FIFA U-17 World Cup India 2017 - Matches - New Caledonia-France|website=FIFA}}</ref> In total, he scored five goals in the tournament.

At the [[2018 UEFA European Under-19 Championship|2018 UEFA U19 Euro]], Gouiri scored two consecutive braces against Turkey<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/match/2024501--turkiye-vs-france/|title=Turkey vs France|date=20 July 2018|website=UEFA}}</ref> and England,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/match/2024506--england-vs-france/|title=England vs France|date=23 July 2018|website=UEFA}}</ref> in the second and third matches of the group stage, respectively.

On 5 September 2023, [[Djamel Belmadi]] announced in the mixed zone that the change of sporting nationality for Gouiri from French to Algerian has been "resolved administratively".<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2023-09-05|date=2023-09-05|first=Léa|language=fr-FR|last=Rek|title=Amine Gouiri représentera l'Algérie, c'est officiel|url=https://foot-algerie.com/2023/09/05/equipes-nationales/cest-officiel-amine-gouiri-representera-lalgerie/}}<!-- auto-translated by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On 26 September 2023, Gouiri announced that he had fully committed to the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gouiri |first1=Amine |title=Avec fierté, je vous annonce ma décision de rejoindre la sélection algérienne 🇩🇿 Je défendrai corps et âme le maillot des Fennecs pour porter haut les couleurs de notre pays et contribuer à écrire les prochaines pages de sa riche histoire. (1/1) |url=https://twitter.com/aminegouiri/status/1706715723689537740 |publisher=Twitter |access-date=26 September 2023 |language=French |date=26 September 2023 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Official: Amine Gouiri chooses to represent Algeria |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2023/official-amine-gouiri-chooses-to-represent-algeria/ |publisher=Get Football News France |access-date=26 September 2023 |date=26 September 2023 }}</ref>

